In his address to Congress, President Trump spoke about the path towards civil rights and the work that still needs to be done. He condemned hate and evil in all forms, referencing recent threats against Jewish community centers and the shooting in Kansas City. He emphasized the importance of unity and strength, stating that a new chapter of American greatness is beginning. The President discussed his plans to bring back jobs, improve infrastructure, and reduce regulations. He also called for the repeal and replacement of Obamacare, reforms to the immigration system, and increased support for the military. President Trump highlighted the importance of education, safety, and the fight against terrorism. He ended his speech by urging Americans to embrace the renewal of the American spirit and to believe in the future of the country.